==English==

===Etymology===
From hiero (Greek hieros-sacred) + phany (Greek phainein-to show)

===Noun===
'''hierophany'''
#[[physical|Physical]] [[manifestation]] of the [[holy]] or [[sacred]].  This manifestation can be in many forms, often in symbols or rituals.  An example of a hierophany would be an [[apparition]] or [[image]] appearing on a window bearing resemblance to the virgin Mary.  Many believers will think that such an apparition is a sacred message sent by God, and will worship it as a sacred item or a holy item.


